From 05064b20135091ff4cb4ccf7c58b022a2e1ecf74 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 18:54:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix urgent webhook field mismatch; make classifier batch
 failures recoverable

lib/notify.js: the urgent Slack/Teams/WhatsApp push read so_what/regulator/tier
(leftover Regulatory-Radar fields that don't exist on pr_items), so every
severity-5 alert went out with a blank action line and undefined payload fields.
Now derives the Action line from pr_angle and builds the payload from the real
PR fields (brand, sentiment, importance, category, coverage spread, deep link).

lib/classify.js: a batch that returned unparseable JSON marked all 25 stories
is_relevant:false, silently burying real coverage. classifyChunk() now splits a
failed batch in half and retries recursively down to a single item, isolating a
poison item to itself. Items the model still never scores are stored as
category:'unclassified' (greppable, counted in logs) rather than as 'other'.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01F4kHoHuaxE7u6WCww7y4VN
